ifornia State University Hayward|Cal-State Hayward]]\n*1975: [[California State University Hayward|Cal-State Hayward]] \n*1976: [[California State University Hayward|Cal-State Hayward]] \n*1977: \n*1978: \n*1979: \n*1980: \n*1981: \n*1982: [[California State University Hayward|Cal-State Hayward]]\n*1983: [[California State University Hayward|Cal-State Hayward]]\n*1984: [[California State University Hayward|Cal-State Hayward]]\n*1985: [[Chico State University|Chico State]]\n*1986: [[Chico State University|Chico State]]\n*1987: [[Chico State University|Chico State]]\n*1988: [[California State University Hayward|Cal-State Hayward]]\n*1989: [[California State University Hayward|Cal-State Hayward]]\n*1990: [[Sonoma State University|Sonoma State]]\n*1991: [[Sonoma State University|Sonoma State]]\n*1993: [[Sonoma State University|Sonoma State]]\n*1995: [[Sonoma State University|Sonoma State]]\n*1996: [[Sonoma State University|Sonoma State]]\n*1997: [[Sonoma State University|Sonoma State]]\n\n===Women's soccer===\n*1982: \n*1983: [[California State University Hayward|Cal-State Hayward]]\n*1984: [[California State University Hayward|Cal-State Hayward]]\n*1985: [[California State University Hayward|Cal-State Hayward]]\n*1986: [[California State University Hayward|Cal-State Hayward]]\n*1987: [[California State University Hayward|Cal-State Hayward]]\n*1988: [[California State University Hayward|Cal-State Hayward (** National Champions **)]]\n\n\n===Women's basketball===\n*1998: [[Sonoma State University|Sonoma State]]\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of defunct college football conferences]]\n* [[California Coast Conference]] (1922\u20131928)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Northern California Athletic Conference|*]]\n[[Category:Sports organizations established in 1925]]\n[[Category:1998 disestablishments in California]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Athletic Conference\n|name = Northern California Athletic Conference\n|short_name = NCAC\n|established = 1925\n|dissolved = 1998\n|logo = Northern California Athletic Conference logo.png\n|logo_size = 150\n|association = [[National Collegiate Athletic Association|NCAA]]\n|division = [[NCAA Division II|Division II]]\n|subdivision =\n|members = 12 (total)\n|sports = \n|mens = \n|womens = \n|region = [[West Coast of the United States|West Coast]]\n|former_names = Far Western Conference (1925&ndash;1982)\n|hq_city = \n|hq_state = \n|commissioner = \n|since = \n|website = \n|color =\n|font_color =\n|map = \n|map_size = \n}}\nThe '''Northern California Athletic Conference''' ('''NCAC'''), a former [[NCAA Division II]] college athletic association that sponsored [[American football]], was formed in 1925. It disbanded in 1998 after the majority of its member schools were forced to drop football.\n\n==History==\nThe NCAC was founded as the '''Far Western Conference''' ('''FWC''') in 1925 by its charter member schools: [[California State University, Fresno|Fresno State]], [[Saint Mary's College of California|Saint Mary's]], [[University of California, Davis|UC Davis]], [[University of Nevada, Reno|Nevada]], [[San Jos\u00e9 State University|San Jose State]] and [[University of the Pacific (United States)|Pacific]].<ref name=cfdw>{{cite web|url=http://www.cfbdatawarehouse.com/data/conference_champs/champions.php?conid=146|publisher=College Football Data Warehouse|accessdate=January 7, 2010|title=Conference Championships: Northern California Athletic Conference}}</ref>\n\nNevada's departure from the conference in 1940 left the conference with only four members; Chico State, Fresno State, College of the Pacific, and UC Davis.<ref>{{cite news|title=Nevada to Quit Far Western Loop|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=A8xYAAAAIBAJ&sjid=lugDAAAAIBAJ&pg=4751,5564426&dq=far-western-conference+san-francisco-state&hl=en|accessdate=5 May 2011|newspaper=Eugene Register-Guard|date=Jan 7, 1940}}</ref> The conference looked to four nominees in Humboldt State, San Francisco State, Santa Barbara State, and California Poly of San Luis Obispo.<ref>{{cite news|title=Nevada Quits But List Grid Game With COP|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=MEgzAAAAIBAJ&sjid=ne4HAAAAIBAJ&pg=6446,2188384&dq=far-western-conference+san-francisco-state&hl=en|accessdate=5 May 2011|newspaper=Lodi News-Sentinel|date=Jan 8, 1940}}</ref>\n\nShortly after [[World War II]], all of these charter members, with the exception of UC Davis, would leave for other conferences, to be replaced by [[San Francisco State University|San Francisco State]], [[California State University, Sacramento|Sacramento State]], [[California State University, East Bay|Hayward State]], [[Southern Oregon University|Southern Oregon]], [[Sonoma State University|Sonoma State]] and [[California State University, Chico|Chico State]].  During the 1990s, each of the universities associated with the California State system chose to disband their football teams in order to comply with [[Title IX]], with the exception of Humboldt State, which added two women's sports to achieve compliance, and Sacramento State University.\n\n==Members==\n[[File:Far Western Conference logo.png|thumb|right]]\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! Institution\n! Location\n! Founded\n! Nickname\n! Joined\n! Left \n! Current<br>conference\n|-\n! [[California State University, Chico|Chico State]]\n| [[Chico, California|Chico, CA]]\n| 1887\n| [[Chico State Wildcats|Wildcats]]\n| 1927\n| 1996\n| [[California Collegiate Athletic Association|CCAA]]\n|-\n! [[California State University, Fresno|Fresno State]]\n| [[Fresno, California|Fresno, CA]]\n| 1911\n| [[Fresno State Bulldogs|Bulldogs]]\n| 1925\n| 1940\n| [[Mountain West Conference|Mountain West]]\n|-\n! [[California State University, East Bay|Hayward State]]\n| [[Hayward, California|Hayward, CA]]\n| 1956\n| [[Cal State East Bay Pioneers|Pioneers]]\n| 1964\n| 1993\n| [[California Collegiate Athletic Association|CCAA]]\n|-\n! [[Humboldt State University|Humboldt State]]\n| [[Arcata, California|Arcata, CA]]\n| 1913\n| [[Humboldt State Lumberjacks|Lumberjacks]]\n| 1930\n| 1996\n| [[California Collegiate Athletic Association|CCAA]]\n|-\n! [[University of Nevada, Reno|Nevada]]\n| [[Reno, Nevada|Reno, NV]]\n| 1874\n| [[Nevada Wolf Pack|Wolf Pack]]\n| 1925<br>1954\n| 1939<br>1968\n| [[Mountain West Conference|Mountain West]]\n|-\n! [[University of the Pacific (United States)|Pacific (CA)]]\n| [[Stockton, California|Stockton, CA]]\n| 1911\n| [[Pacific Tigers|Tigers]]\n| 1925\n| 1942\n| [[West Coast Conference|West Coast]]\n|-\n! [[California State University, Sacramento|Sacramento State]]\n| [[Sacramento, California|Sacramento, CA]]\n| 1947\n| [[Sacramento State Hornets|Hornets]]\n| 1954\n| 1984\n| [[Big Sky Conference|Big Sky]]\n|-\n! [[Saint Mary's College of California|Saint Mary's]]\n| [[Moraga, California|Moraga, CA]]\n| 1863\n| [[Saint Mary's Gaels|Gaels]]\n| 1925\n| 1928\n| [[West Coast Conference|West Coast]]\n|-\n! [[San Francisco State University|San Francisco State]]\n| [[San Francisco, California|San Francisco, CA]]\n| 1899\n| [[San Francisco State Gators|Gators]]\n| 1947\n| 1995\n| [[California Collegiate Athletic Association|CCAA]]\n|-\n! [[San Jos\u00e9 State University|San Jose State]]\n| [[San Jose, California|San Jose, CA]]\n| 1857\n| [[San Jose State Spartans|Spartans]]\n| 1929\n| 1934\n| [[Mountain West Conference|Mountain West]]\n|-\n! [[Sonoma State University|Sonoma State]]\n| [[Rohnert Park, California|Rohnert Park, CA]]\n| 1960\n| [[Sonoma State Seawolves|Cossacks (now Seawolves)]]\n| 1971<br>1983\n| <br>1998\n| [[California Collegiate Athletic Association|CCAA]]\n|-\n! [[Southern Oregon Raiders football|Southern Oregon]]\n| [[Ashland, Oregon|Ashland, OR]]\n| 1872\n| [[Southern Oregon Raiders|Raiders]]\n| 1947\n| 1954\n| [[Cascade Collegiate Conference|Cascade Collegiate]]\n|-\n! [[University of California, Davis|UC Davis]]\n| [[Davis, California|Davis, CA]]\n| 1905\n| [[UC Davis Aggies|Aggies]]\n| 1925\n| 1992\n| [[Big Sky Conference|Big Sky]]\n|}\n\n===Membership timeline===\n<timeline>\nDateFormat = yyyy\nImageSize  = width:800 height:auto barincrement:25\nPeriod     = from:1925 till:1998\nTimeAxis   = orientation:horizontal\nPlotArea   = right:30 left:0 bottom:50 top:5\n\nColors = id:barcolor value:rgb(0.99,0.7,0.7)\n         id:line     value:black\n         id:bg       value:white\n\nPlotData=\n  width:20 textcolor:black shift:(5,-5) anchor:from fontsize:s\n\n  bar:1  color:powderblue from:1925 till:end text:[[Chico State Wildcats|Chico State]] (1927\u20131996)\n  bar:2  color:powderblue from:1925 till:1992 text:[[UC Davis Aggies|UC Davis]] (1925\u20131992)\n  bar:3  color:powderblue from:1925 till:1928 text:[[Saint Mary's Gaels|Saint Mary's (CA)]] (1925\u20131928)\n  bar:4  color:powderblue from:1925 till:1939 text:[[Nevada Wolf Pack|Nevada]] (1925\u20131939, 1954\u20131968)\n  bar:4  color:powderblue from:1954 till:1968 text:[[Nevada Wolf Pack|Nevada]] \n  bar:5  color:powderblue from:1925 till:1942 text:[[Pacific Tigers football|Pacific (CA)]] (1925\u20131942)\n  bar:6  color:powderblue from:1925 till:1940 text:[[Fresno State Bulldogs|Fresno State]] (1925\u20131940)\n  bar:7  color:powderblue from:1927 till:1928 text:[[San Francisco Dons|San Francisco]] (1927\u20131928)\n  bar:8  color:powderblue from:1929 till:1934 text:[[San Jose State Spartans|San Jose State]] (1929\u20131934)\n  bar:9  color:powderblue from:1930 till:end text:[[Humboldt State Lumberjacks|Humboldt State]] (1930\u20131996)\n  bar:10  color:powderblue from:1947 till:1954 text:[[Southern Oregon Raiders|Southern Oregon]] (1947\u20131954)\n  bar:11  color:powderblue from:1947 till:1995 text:[[San Francisco State Gators|San Francisco State]] (1947\u20131995)\n  bar:12  color:powderblue from:1954 till:1984 text:[[Sacramento State Hornets|Sacramento State]] (1954\u20131984)\n  bar:13  color:powderblue from:1971 till:1972 text:[[Sonoma State Seawolves|Sonoma State]] (1971, 1983\u20131998)\n  bar:13  color:powderblue 